values: I still live! Bwhahahaha! er... nothing.. that was it... for now.

Okay, so it has been a while since I've actually wrote anything in this journal. I'd like to point out that I've been having issues. Lol, like it would be the first time, nor will it be the last. For the lack of better words, I am semi homeless, granted I have one parent that still has anything to do with me and I have moved in with my mother. Most of you know the situation, yays for you, for those who don't, I surely don't want to talk about it. I just have my laptop, phone, clothes I left at my mother's house, and my car, luckily I had most of my winter clothes stored at mum's place. I have my health, some sense of sanity, the phrase "Meh, it was only stuff." Granted it was almost a lifetime of junk, but it was still mine. Sad thing is, I mourn the loss of my cd collection, games, ps1 and my books. What I miss the most is my books. You people know how much I love to read, and those who had ever been to my apartment knew that the books were piled everywhere, on the floor, countertops, couch, entertainment center... etc. Life's a bitch and then we go on... I've gotten some donated scrubs and slacks to wear to work, granted they are baggy as hell and I didn't think they made women's pants this long, but I have enough clothes to make it through. I've been waiting on different places to have sales so I can get some more jeans, cause I think I have four pair, a couple pair of track pants, and two pairs of khakis. I've also built my cheap tshirt collection back up. I don't care what you say about walmart tshirts, stfu and have a nice day, I like them, cause they tend to have "accidents" if my mother decides grabs clothes from my hamper to make sure the washers have a full load. I do my own laundry thank you very much, but there's times when she doesn't think she has enough clothes of the light colored or dark colored clothes, so she grabs some of mine. I've lost my misfits tshirt cause of that... yeah... it was black with the crimson ghost face on the front, at one point, now it's a dull pink with tinges of grey in it and the white "crimson ghost" face on the front. She's lost several tshirts like that, absent minded, adding bleach to the wrong washer... -le sigh- I have to steal her normal shirts and wash them so she won't bleach them, or have bleach spots some how on them, cause she also puts too much of the color safe bleach and some how ruins her shirts as well. Example? She used to have a dark purple shirt, like royal purple, now it's bright "sherbert" orange. I've made an attempt at drawing a little, but I have no motive, nor inspiration. (No, we're still not doing "Butcher Knife" until you figure out what the hell they're doing and you make a script or a outline, Sam.) I also bought a small wacom, a 6x8" medium Bamboo Fun, just to play around with until I get the feeling for it. (The old tablet was turned into a chew toy by four pain in the butt kittens.) So, let's see, cheap used wacom tablet... semi talked about being without a home of my own... What is left? The kittens are still a pain in the ass. I'm reading, "Pride and Prejudice and Zombies", "The Zombie Survival Guide", "World War Z", "Swallowing Darkness", "Stolen", "Darker Angels", "Dark Stranger", "The Renegade Hunter"... Yeah, blame the A.D.D. for the skipping. The finished pile is a lot worse. Lol. I did back up the desktop a couple of times and kept the hard drive handy at mum's should anything happen, thankfully I did, so I don't have to worry about most of my programs should something happen to the laptop. I'm sleeping on a couch with a hideaway bed, thankfully a queen size bed, so I don't have to worry about my feet hanging over the end, I can just stretch across the darn thing, though the cats don't think I need all that space and sleep around me. I can see my two kittens sleeping next to me, but my mom's two cats drive me up the wall at night by thinking the bed is a trampoline or the underbelly of the bed is their new scratching post. I started several projects, knitting wise, the usual headband/wrap thingies, just cause everybody is asking for one, and I have to tell them, buy the color(s) you want and I can make it for you, no cost. I may add in a thin scarf with the left over thread if I have enough for it. I have spent more time out at the casino that what should be possible for a person who gets bored easily by the machines. I get a large, I should say "venti" caramel macchiato for the trouble of taking mum out there, or a slice of pizza (mushrooms, italian sausage, black olives, extra cheese and onions, my favorite, yum! I'm hungry now, dammit... ) I did win like two hundred sixty dollars combined, in a few minutes. I was given a five by mum, and I wandered off to a game that had dragons on it (yes I know, stfu) and it gave me one hundred eighty-five within two spins. I cashed out and put my five back in the machine at another spot and wound up with the money, and wandered off to sit around to wait on mum to finish playing. I haven't won much after that, then again I haven't been playing that much, more or less wandering around the casino for good measure maybe? Um, um, movies... I can't think of anything. What I watched lately was, (500)Days of Summer, Splinter, and Witches Hammer . I'm gonna watch Tokyo Gore Police, and Boy Eats Girl again, probably tomorrow or so. Comics... um, lol the boss would probably disown me if I didn't put Shonen Punk , though it just ended, still a good read imho... Fragile Gravity , Theater Hopper ,and yet another one that has run it's course but still fun to look at, Housd I'm done...
Fluffybabies! they're 6 weeks old now.... XD and not much bigger than that pic now.

Gonna be one of those long days. I put this on the front door of my department.

'nuff said~

So, yeah, for those who noticed I went missing, yeah, sorry for short notice, but two idiots crushed my broadband card, cellphone, and flashdrive, with my unassembled futon in a box. So needless to say I got a new phone and having to return calls to you people who have left voicemails. XD Sad thing is that I still havent finished putting the new futon together, or push the old stuff to the side so i can set up the damn thing.

I don't exactly know how to say that I had fun the other thursday, without having to make the excuse that my phone and broadband card was crushed without it sounding too lame after not sending a message or email why I was missing. Its not like I was hiding or anything. Maybe I just creeped him out... -snickers- wouldnt be the first time, but I tell you people that I dont talk that much when I first meet people.

um, yeah, i'm gonna go play on youtube or draw now.


I'm done, I'm out~

I got nothing, I mean interesting. We really dont celebrate holidays except for the nieces and nephews, but the adults just buy crap when its on sale then hand it over unwrapped. I did, however, recieve many wrapped presents from family members... Two skull hoodies, a couple of skull keychains, several skull earrings (since I do have nine piercings in each ear), two DS games (one I've beaten twice since christmas), a pair of boots made from recycle plastic bottles (I like 'em they have buckles!), some more yarn (like a twenty gallon tote, full to the brim wasnt enough yarn), um, lets see, um, a little purse that has skulls on it and $45 sent through other parties from my father... Yeah, that just got put off to the side. I got myself a new messenger bag (it was on sale and it had metal on the loophandles instead of plastic) and a new mp3 player (a four gig and plays video, lol instead of my old one gig that just spazzed out if you tried to restart the song you were listening to, plus the voice record button was on the side, so I had a few clips of my horrid singing, in the middle of a coversation, or the sounds of the chimes, bells, and music that the machines at the casino make. XD Needless to say that just comes up weird while listening over your headset.
I'm done, I'm out~

So, a few things... Have I gotten tired of school yet? Yes, and no. I love learning but they say our class is behind yet they want to feed us to the wolves, so to speak, the second years. Have I hit a point in life where I question every waking moment? Yes, but it's mainly the things I've done or hadnt done in my life, and who doesnt? I just reassure myself that I am a normal person with a passion. I don't regret anything that I have done schoolwise, but I have given up on a normal life for the pursuit of this career up til now and possibly the rest of my life. Have I given up on dating? Kinda for the moment, with school, stress at work, and the usual crap with the family... Have I given up on love? No, not truly... But lust has been a funny subject in my book. I lust after two people and actually like one of them enough to be close to love. At least I think its love, it could be heartburn for all I know, cuz all I know really is lust. I think I'll know love when I get near it, but now i'm sure its just a bad crush...
Edit: A little poem, "I left to pursue, i chased, got what i want, but after a few days, i got a pyscho bitch like you." -bows- screw following what i thought was love cuz it really was heartburn, lol. XD I'm down a person to lust after, so who's next?
Anyways, I'm pretty sure none of that made any sense but I dont care cuz it's my journal entry so bite me. -tilts head to the side and smiles- 'k, thanks for the time. Bai, come again. XD

It's been a while back, at least over six months since the waterheater leaked in the apartment above me... There's a crap load of water damage to my ceiling but luckly there wasn't a mold problem... where i live the frigging place is too dry anyhow to mold half the time. -shrugs- Anyways, gonna go see someone about a piercing... X3
Oh and if anyone finds a copy of Sundown: The Vampire in Retreat... XD i'll love you... forever... i was about to say something else but yeah... I was reminded earlier this week that I didn't have it... OMFG... It's got Bruce Campbell, who is my brothers and my god... XD Vampires and b-rate movie... two of my major obsessions...
XD I also learned I'm gonna an aunt three times over this year... yay!

Okay, so nothing new, won $114 at the casino with one dollar... so Ha.... woo. Um, let's see, attempted to make a new ID -shakes her head- turned out something weird. OMFG... I watched Match Mistress... XD and the lovely lady... um... wetdream come true for some people -coughs- and shiny! 8B
I took my bar exams, I've lurked in class, now I'm out for a bit to help take care of Mum, so nothing really truly going on beyond having to work on papers as usual, catch up on my reading and knitting. Working on a pattern called Marley's Chains, Jacob Marley from the Christmas Carol as if you didn't know. I'm also working on a baby blanket for two of my honorary siblings, tho one's late and one's a bit early, XD stfu, it takes me a little while because I only work on this stuff when I have free time, like when I'm supposed to be studying but knitting, watching tv, and reading the textbook at the same time. Possibly eating pocky at the same time but that's the norm, I mean, c'mon I got a mini pocky wall.
Anyways, I spent the day annoying the piss out of people, but hell it's not that hard around here. I'll get back to the usual movies and such here in a few weeks when everything calms down and I ACTUALLY watch anything other than Torchwood. Damn my fangirlness for john barrowman :B XD
I'm out~


P.S. Like a goober I've been listening to 80s music I grew up on. 8B

Okay, so the normal. Nothing new so far... I like classes... papers already, research papers none the less, bleh. Anyways, so this past week has been fun, not really. I updated my crap over on OKCupid, nothing big, I actually put up a small blog explaining myself, sorta. I worked and finished my six papers within two days, which wasn't hard and already sent them in to be graded. I should be told by Monday what I made on them. The biggest fun that I had this week was being woke up at four a.m. Saturday morning, mind you I just got off of work at one a.m., took a shower and crawled under the afgan by two-thirty or so, falling asleep by three a.m. It was Mum, calling to tell me to bring her a change of clothes, and that she would be in the ER... for those who don't know, both she and I work at the county hospital in my hometown on the weekends. Anywho, back to Mum, well she had stepped outback into the smoking area, where you can see the back of the hospital and the pasture that an old doctor (the doctor who delievered my brothers and our father, who has passed on) owned. Usually if you step out back you can see deer wandering by. (yes, we're pretty much out in the country so leave it be... XD If you haven't heard me talk, I have a "country drawl" if I don't pay attention to what I say or enunciate correctly, if I correct myself enough I sadly bring another accent in that I have no clue where it comes from.) Back to Mum yet again, anyways she stepped off the little concrete porch area, and slipped into a little drainage ditch that had formed from the run off from the gutters and years and years of rain. Needless to say that it has been raining for about three days straight before she stepped over in that direction. She would have been fine if she hadn't straightened out one of her legs while trying to catch herself, but she did. She slid, twisted her ankle in a weird direction and broke the lower part of her fibula, just a little above her ankle. She called saying that she didn't know if she had broke it or not but she just wanted some new clothes and for me to pick her up to take her home. Well, I get there, and they say she has broke it, the strap a stabilizer boot on her and we go home, long enough to take a nap then head to the next hospital over, because our hospital doesn't have an orthopedic section. We get there, they look at the films and she's admitted, surgery is the next day and I'm left to go back to Mum's house thirty minutes away, to get clothes and the essentials for an overnight stay, for her. I completely forgot stuff for myself, but after that I stayed with her except when they took her to surgery, when I left to get something to eat. I waited, they brought her back a few hours, being nearly five hours only to observe her because her blood pressure and heartrate was low, but hell those are already low on her as is, plus the anesthesia making it just a little lower than normal, but that's only because she was sleeping. They keep her another night and I just wait for a bit, they let her go the next day after we ended up getting a wheelchair and walker, which now I call Mum "Hoppalong" everytime she's moving around. Btw, the ended up putting a plate in on the break, to set it, she's also go eleven staples going down the side of her ankle and lower leg and she's grumpy as hell when I try and do the dressing change, tho it's not from the pain. It's just the usual, I can never do anything right in her eyes, even when I'm taking the time to pause and just breathe before I end up blowing up on her, unlike what she's done to me. I've done my best, I've kept my cool, but hell, eh... for those who know Mum, you know wtf I'm talking about. I think I'm done for the rant other than I think my legs hurt a little, but that's from pushing the damn wheelchair around the casino... lmfao.

Okay, so, as usual... I got zip. XD Nada, nothing, empty hands here buddy. Anyways, since I've been on break, I've taken the chance I haven't had in a while to actually just hang out with Mum. Unfortunately that just means a lot of sleeping, eating and hanging around the house except on Monday and Wednesday nights. Those nights we head out to the casino, cuz if not we freeze our asses off stepping outside to smoke a cig, since, yes Mum does smoke... but she doesn't want the smell in the house. -just sits there and stares before shrugging her shoulders- Don't give me that funny look, I know, just kinda like I'm not allowed to smoke in my own car, she doesn't want that smell of stale smoke inside. -shakes her head slowly- Back to what I was saying, we go out to the casino... and stay out there from maybe three in the morning till almost two in the afternoon. So needless to say that I sleep maybe 4 hours then go back to functioning somewhat for the rest of the day till ... when ever she wanted me to go get lunch or dinner, depending on how long she slept. I kept myself preoccupied by just drawing and trying to get used to drawing on this laptop just using the touchpad, which I have to say I've gotten a little better. For those who didn't know I have a lousy spot over at Deviant Art. But those who ask nicely (or I just feel like it) get to see what I've just drawn on pencil and paper which I keep hidden (somewhat) online. I suck at drawing cuz I get influnced by other people's drawings then try it on my own, and I just make it look godawful but still... at least I try.


So yeah for those who haven't seen my hair in a while ... . Front half is dark brown/black and semi long. the back half is blonde/platinum in some spots and short. The pigtails are because I can't pull all of my hair into a ponytail and the back and front falling out of the rubberband.

I'll be back later to finish this oh so interesting update. and I know somewhere therese someone singing that lambchops song now an it's stuck in there head... -cackle, chokecough, and wanders off to finish work-

Okay, so I took the week off. Granted, I waited till it was my birthday weekend to do it. XD Doesn't mean much, still have a crapload of homework to turn in, catching up on stuff shouldn't be so bad. I didn't do much other than sleep, run errands and well... shop, but still. I paid my electric and net bills for now, still gotta pay the new phone bill when it arrives, pay rent and move the last of my b-day presents from mom's to my apartment. Not much more than the last time, just a new scanner/printer combo thingie... That's about it on the whole new gift frontier, bought some magazines and a couple of books and Mom took me to the movies the day of my birthday. We saw the "Covenant". It was so so, could have done without a few scenes but it was basic plots... Boy meets girl, boy meets rival, boy has powers that eat away at his body if he uses too much, boy gets girl, boy and rival fight. Nuff said.
Watched a little weird movie before going to the movies that day, called "Once Upon A Wedding". I missed the first part of it but it kinda got decent from the middle on. Romeo and Juilet style love, cept, he's just a fisherman, a peasant, and she's the daughter of El Comandante~ Dictator of the island. The bad thing is, the water is poisoned so the fishermen are poor as hell because of the dead fish. El Comadante, sits in a bit of a fog through the movie, letting Pineda, his second in command, run just about everything, including Margarita, the daughter of El Comadante, who is already engaged and about to be married in a week or so. I missed the part where Margarita accidently hits Rogelio, the fisherman with her car. It's a decent comedy, but the serious parts actually just can't be taken serious. Though I do like the part where one of the fisherman's friends, Carmelita makes Pineda eat his prized koi.

I'm Done... ~
P.S. Should I be afraid that there's going to be an "Evil Dead: The Musical"?

Okay, So nothing new as always... Exactly a week till my birthday, so blech on that, which means here comes the "Do you feel a year older" or " How old are you now?" questions start... hell if i know how old i am... I stopped counting at 13... didn't care passed then. So what, year older, yet another year has passed by, next year will still be the same.
As I was saying, nothing new... I did watch this cute little movie, at least I thought it was cute and all with the happy ending and such, and a guy playing Cary Grant as an imaginary friend to a lonely guy. The movie's called a Touch of Pink. At the beginning, we start out with seemingly normal guy, a photographer, living his life with his love, and every once in a while talking to his imaginary friend, who by the way, is supposed to be Cary Grant. Btw, suggestion if anyone wants to watch a couple of movies: "Girl" and "Bandwagon".

Girl is about a girl from West Hills (rich neighborhood) who through so far came off to be a geek, and she hears her friends are in a band. she goes to hear them play, from there she falls into the indie scene, where she falls in love with a up and coming rock singer. From there she goes through a journey of discovering herself.
Bandwagon is a journey of an unknown band, Circus Monkey. In the beginning, we start with the leader, who has stagefright and can't play or sing when someone looks at him. From there he builds a band of local rejects and trying to build their name up to fame.

They're great movies if you're into unsigned, unknown bands.
